	"packageName": "@arcscord/error",
	"packageVersion": "3.0.0",
	"readme": [
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "# @arcscord/error\n\n[![npm version](https://badge.fury.io/js/@arcscord%2Ferror.svg)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@arcscord/error)\n[![Discord](https://discord.com/api/guilds/1012097557532528791/widget.png?style=shield)](https://discord.gg/4geBanVWGR)\n\nResult-style error handling for TypeScript, inspired by Go. Instead of throwing exceptions, functions return a "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Result<T, E>`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " tuple: either "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`[null, value]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " on success or "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`[error, null]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " on failure. The caller destructs the tuple and handles the error explicitly — no try/catch, no silent propagation.\n\nThis pattern makes error paths visible in function signatures and forces you to handle failures at the call site. It pairs well with TypeScript's discriminated unions: the type of "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`value`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " is only accessible when "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`error`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " is "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`null`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", so the compiler guides you toward correct handling.\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@arcscord/error`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " is used by the entire arcscord ecosystem. \n\n## Install\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```sh\npnpm add @arcscord/error\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Example\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\nimport type { Result } from \"@arcscord/error\";\nimport { error, ok } from \"@arcscord/error\";\n\nfunction divide(a: number, b: number): Result<number, Error> {\n  if (b === 0)\n    return error(new Error(\"Division by zero\"));\n  return ok(a / b);\n}\n\nconst [err, result] = divide(10, 2);\nif (err) {\n  console.error(err.message);\n}\nelse {\n  console.log(result); // 5\n}\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Links\n\n- [Documentation](https://arcscord.dev/packages/error)\n- [API reference](https://arcscord.dev/api?package=error)\n\n## License\n\nMIT"
		}
	],
